# README badges

When creating or updating a project README, always include a badge row near the top (directly under the title) using shields.io-style badges.

Include badges for:

1. **Live demo / deployment** — link to the production URL (e.g. Vercel, Netlify)
2. **Core stack** — every major technology in use (framework, build tool, language, styling, etc.)

Format:

```markdown
# Project Name

[![Live Demo](https://img.shields.io/badge/Live%20Demo-<url-host>-000?style=flat&logo=vercel&logoColor=white)](https://...)
[![React](https://img.shields.io/badge/React-18-61DAFB?style=flat&logo=react&logoColor=black)](https://react.dev)
```

Rules:

- Use `style=flat` and official logos where available
- Link each badge to the relevant project site or live URL
- Keep version numbers accurate to `package.json` or config files
- Update badges when the stack or deployment URL changes
